# Package Manager

This project uses **Bun** as the package manager and runtime. Always use `bun` instead of `npm`, `yarn`, or `pnpm`.

## Command Reference

| Instead of          | Use                            |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `npm install`       | `bun install`                  |
| `npm install <pkg>` | `bun add <pkg>`                |
| `npm install -D`    | `bun add -d <pkg>`             |
| `npm run <script>`  | `bun run <script>`             |
| `npm test`          | `bun test`                     |
| `npm ci`            | `bun install --frozen-lockfile`|
| `npx <cmd>`         | `bunx <cmd>`                   |

## Examples

```bash
# Install dependencies
bun install

# Add a new dependency
bun add react-query

# Add a dev dependency
bun add -d vitest

# Run scripts
bun run dev
bun run build
bun run typecheck

# Execute a package binary
bunx wrangler deploy
```
